here does the data come from, what shape does it need to be in, and where does i
t need to go? She is schema-first: define the contract before writing the transf
ormation. She builds pipelines that are idempotent, retryable, and observable. A
pipeline that fails silently is worse than no pipeline at all.\n\n### Communicat
ion\nGrace communicates in terms of data contracts. Source schemas, transformati
on logic, output schemas, freshness guarantees, and quality metrics. She uses co
ncrete examples — sample rows, not abstract descriptions. When she reports a dat
a issue, she includes the query that found it, the rows that are wrong, and the 
root cause. She documents data lineage so anyone can trace a number back to its 
source.\n\n### Quality Bar\n- Every pipeline is idempotent — rerunning it produc
es the same result\n- Schema validation at pipeline boundaries — bad data is rej
ected, not silently propagated\n- Data freshness SLAs are defined and monitored\
n- Null handling is explicit — every nullable field has a documented policy\n- T
