y\n\n1. **Data Generation:** Synthetic daily market snapshots for 14 Kalshi-styl
e markets across Economics, Crypto, Politics, Weather, Entertainment, and Financ
ial categories.\n2. **Signal Generation:** Each strategy's Python-ported logic s
cans every market/day and generates entry signals when thresholds are met.\n3. *
*Trade Simulation:** On signal entry, the engine simulates buying/selling at the
day's mid price and exits after a 5-day hold period.\n4. **P&L Calculation:** Pr
ofit/Loss = (exit_price - entry_price) × contracts. For NO positions, NO mid pri
ces are used.\n5. **Metrics:** Sharpe ratio uses trade return percentages; max d
rawdown tracks cumulative P&L peaks.\n\n## Notes\n\n- These results use **synthe
tic data** for infrastructure validation. Live backtests will use actual Kalshi 
price history from Bob's database pipeline.\n- The `economic_momentum` strategy 
uses mock forecast divergences until real nowcast data is integrated.\n- `arbitr
age` signals are rare in synthetic data because YES+NO prices are generated to s
um to ~100.\n",
